<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f107703924130383">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=16795&amp;mid=107703924130383">Druid Thought</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=16795&amp;mid=107703924130383#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Tue, Feb 17th 12:33 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=192354"><span id="Sage">Bigskyn</span></a><br /><b><span id="Sage">Sage</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">62 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.65]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I used DKP last night on a raid to get this as a druid. <br/><br/>First time our guild had taken TZ down (1st attempt -- woot !!) I've passed on the VZ neck even though it had better resists and a more &quot;druid friendly&quot; effect with MP4 (have ornate boots -- same effect)but couldn't let this go for the following reasons:<br/><br/>First, mana and hp go without saying. <br/><br/>Second, the strength and dex. Wow. If ever there is a stat that my druid needed to raise, its there. Horribly important to me as a druid? Not as much as some stats, but great to raise them none - the - less.<br/><br/>Third, regen 3. Is it going to save me when I'm being whooped up on or have a severe DoT laying waste to me? Nope. I cannot begin to count, however, the number of times I've been nearly on my deathbed and trying to keep tanks alive. No time to heal me, so this is a neat little addition.&nbsp;&nbsp;For soloing, the regen is extra - nifty as it will help take care of the occasional smack I take running things in circles.<br/><br/>Fourth, resists. As a druid I can self-buff cold and fire resists mightily. Magic and poison resists seem to be the two (with a similar nod to disease) that I need to raise the most. Those DoT's and nukes kill me far more than the melee.<br/><br/>Now finally a small apology to the one melee class in my guild that I think (in hindsight) might have found a better use for this than my druid self (not that one would have ended up with it in our dkp system, but that's neither here-nor-there). Yes, the oft-overlooked rangers.  Warriors and knights are generally maxing their str and dex at this level and get all the tasty buffs in raids. Rangers and their bows would surely benefit from the str and dex here.<br/><br/>In any case, not meaning to open up one of those &quot;which class should get it threads&quot; just pointing out where it might have been most useful in our guild at our stage of equipping.  This is a nice piece for anyone who has the points of favor to get it though. Enjoy.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />WoW--Hunter <a href=HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?10438 target=akztarg> Betrothed</a> (Perenolde)<br/><br/>Retired Druid Bigskyn (EQ-Kane Bayle)<br/>Retired Warrior Thumpn (EQ-Kane Bayle)</td></tr>
